-- Carl Zeiss Meditec Seeks Takeovers, Boersen-Zeitung Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-05-11T17:47:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/carl-zeiss-meditec-seeks-takeovers-boersen-zeitung-reports.html
Carl Zeiss Meditec AG (AFX)  plans to spend
its cash reserves on acquisitions,  Boersen-Zeitung  reported in a
preview of an article to be published tomorrow, citing an
interview with Chief Executive Officer Christian Mueller.  The medical laser- and surgery products-maker has 110
million euros ($142 million) in cash reserves to spend, and may
seek additional funding through bonds or loans should a larger
takeover be possible, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt at 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
